[thinking] **Considering actor system functionality**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about the actor class in the test and whether it relies on reflection. The Props[MetadataActor]() macro or classTag might be part of the public API, but it could involve reflection, which complicates testing. I wonder if I can avoid creating an actor by using system.deadLetters, which is an ActorRef. I’m also curious if the ActorRefSerializer can serialize deadLetters and if provider.resolveActorRef can successfully resolve them. It seems like it probably can!
[thinking] 
